18 1. The National Association of the Deaf;
19 2. The Hearing Loss Association of America; and
20 3. The Maryland Association of the Deaf;
21 (6) Encourage partnerships and collaborations with information service
22 providers to help provide virtual access to information and research;
23 (7) Form a Deaf Culture Digital Library Advisory Board to provide advice
24 on initiatives that further advance the mission and goals of the Deaf Culture Digital
25 Library and the majority of whose members are deaf or hard of hearing and selected from
26 the following entities:
27 (i) County library systems;
28 (ii) The State Library Agency;
